 produce directly to neighbors, local households, and even local spaza shops or food vendors. You\'ll take orders via your smartphone and deliver them locally. This business starts extremely small and can be scaled as you gain experience and capital. You will offer basic digital marketing services to local businesses. This includes setting up and managing their social media pages (e.g., Facebook, WhatsApp Business profile), taking attractive photos of their products or services using your smartphone, writing simple promotional posts, and helping them engage with customers online. You can also teach basic digital literacy to business owners. You\'ll charge a small monthly fee per client, making your smartphone your main tool.', 'This business leverages your smartphone as the primary tool for communication and marketing. It requires almost no upfront cash for inventory, rent, or equipment, as you\'re facilitating sales, not owning stock. It directly utilizes your marketing skill and farming interest. It\'s part-time and flexible. This directly uses your farming interest. It requires minimal upfront capital, relying on repurposed items and small seed packets. Your marketing skill is vital for direct sales in your community. It\'s part-time and offers flexibility. This directly utilizes your marketing skill and your smartphone. It requires virtually no cash capital beyond keeping your smartphone charged and connected. It’s a part-time service that can grow as you gain clients and experience.', 'M180 M75 M120', 'Week 1:** Map out local farmers, understand their produce, quantities, and availability. Use your sm', 'en', '2025-11-13 19:38:49', NULL),
(89, 5, 'Marketing', 'Farming', 'Smartphone: ✓', '-29.389316, 27.524125', 'part-time', 'Small-scale farmers in the Thaba-Bosiu area often struggle to find consistent buyers and market their produce effectively, leading to waste or low prices. Consumers in nearby Maseru seek fresh, local produce but lack direct access to farmers. Many small businesses, guesthouses, and farmers in the Thaba-Bosiu region lack the time, skills, or knowledge to effectively market themselves online and reach more customers through social media. Small-scale farmers often lack access to timely, practical, and localized agricultural information, such as best planting practices, pest control tips, weather forecasts, or current market prices for their produce.', 'Thaba-Bosiu Harvest Hub Thaba-Bosiu Digital Connect Basotho Agri-Advice', 'You will act as an intermediary, connecting local farmers directly with buyers (individuals, small grocery shops, restaurants) in Maseru and the surrounding areas. Using your smartphone, you\'ll communicate with farmers to know what produce is available, take photos, list items online (e.g., WhatsApp groups, local social media pages), and collect orders. You will coordinate pick-up directly from the farm or arrange for a central meeting point. Your income will be a commission (e.g., 10-20%) on each sale. This leverages your marketing skills to bridge the gap between rural producers and urban consumers. You will offer basic social media marketing services to local farmers, small shops, guesthouses, and tourism attractions. This includes creating engaging content (photos and short videos taken with your smartphone), managing their social media pages (Facebook, WhatsApp Business), and posting updates about their products, services, or farm offerings. You will help them tell their story and connect with potential customers. You\'ll charge a small monthly retainer or a per-post/project fee. You will become a local go-to source for agricultural information. Using your smartphone, you\'ll curate and disseminate valuable farming tips, practical advice, and market insights relevant to the Thaba-Bosiu area. This can be done through free WhatsApp groups, community social media pages, or short video tutorials you create with your phone. Once you\'ve built a following and trust, you can introduce premium services, such as personalized advisory sessions (e.g., via call or WhatsApp chat for a small fee), or connecting farmers to specific government agricultural programs or NGO support for a referral fee.', 'Skills & Interests:** Directly combines your marketing skills with your interest in farming. Capital:** Requires virtually no startup cash, only your existing smartphone and minimal data/airtime for communication. No inventory is held. Location:** Thaba-Bosiu is a farming area close to the Maseru market, ideal for this brokerage model. Flexibility:** Can be started part-time, building client relationships gradually. Skills & Interests:** Directly uses your marketing skills and can be applied to your farming interest. Capital:** Requires only your existing smartphone and minimal data. You are selling your time and expertise. Location:** Many local businesses in semi-rural areas need this support to reach wider markets. Scalability:** Can start with one or two clients and grow as your reputation builds. Skills & Interests:** Leverages your interest in farming and your marketing skills to disseminate information. Capital:** Requires only your existing smartphone and minimal data for research and communication. Impact:** Empowers local farmers with knowledge, potentially increasing their yields and incomes. Scalability:** Can start with free content, building an audience, before monetizing.', 'Equipment/Tools: Smartphone (owned) – M0 Initial Stock: M0 (commission-based model) Licenses/Permits', 'Week 1-2:** Identify 3-5 local farmers, understand their produce and availability. Create a dedicate', 'en', '2025-11-13 19:42:25', NULL);
INSERT INTO `recommendations` (`id`, `user_id`, `skills`, `interests`, `capital`, `location`, `availability`, `problem_solved`, `business_title`, `business_description`, `reason_for_fit`, `estimated_capital`, `suggested_schedule`, `language`, `created_at`, `rating`) VALUES
(90, 5, 'Carpentry', 'Farming', 'Smartphone: ✓', '-29.389313, 27.524122', 'weekends-only', 'Residents and small businesses in the Mazenod/Thaba-Bosiu area need affordable, reliable carpentry services for repairs, custom small projects, and furniture maintenance, but often struggle to find local artisans or afford new items. Local farmers and home gardeners in the Mazenod/Thaba-Bosiu area need practical, affordable wooden items like seedling trays, small storage boxes, garden stakes, raised bed frames, or basic animal housing (e.g., small chicken coops). Mass-produced items can be expensive, and custom options are scarce. Many residents in peri-urban areas want to establish home gardens for food security and fresh produce but lack the knowledge, time, or initial setup assistance.', 'Mazenod Mobile Carpentry & Repair Lerato\'s Rural Woodcraft Mazenod Green Thumbs Helper', 'Offer on-site repair and custom carpentry services for homes and small businesses on weekends. This includes fixing broken furniture, repairing wooden doors/windows, building small shelves, or creating simple custom wood items. Your smartphone will be used for communication, scheduling, and marketing via local WhatsApp groups and social media. Materials for each job will be purchased after receiving payment or provided by the customer. Focus your carpentry skills on creating small, functional wooden items specifically for local farming and gardening needs. This could include seedling trays, small compost bins, garden markers, simple fencing panels, or custom-sized raised garden beds. You can operate on a \"made-to-order\" basis, where customers provide or pay for materials upfront. Your smartphone is key for showcasing your work (photos), taking orders, and coordinating deliveries. Offer basic home garden setup and advisory services on weekends. This includes helping clients plan small vegetable patches, advise on suitable crops for the local climate, assist with soil preparation, and planting. Your carpentry skills can be leveraged to offer add-on services like building raised garden beds, simple trellises, or compost bins (referencing Idea #2\'s material model). You will provide knowledge and labor, while the client provides seeds, seedlings, and gardening tools. Your smartphone will be for consultations, sharing tips, and scheduling.', 'This directly leverages your carpentry skills and requires virtually no upfront cash beyond your existing tools (assumed) and smartphone. The \"weekends-only\" availability is perfect for household repairs or small projects that people defer during the week. In peri-urban areas like Mazenod, there\'s a constant need for maintenance and affordable solutions, aligning with FinScope findings on the prevalence of small, informal service providers. This idea combines your carpentry skills with your interest in farming, addressing a specific niche in your semi-rural location. The demand for local food production and small-scale farming is significant in Lesotho (as highlighted by agricultural development initiatives). Operating on weekends allows for production without interfering with weekday commitments. Operating on a pre-order/customer-material model ensures zero cash outlay for initial stock. This leverages your interest in farming and the growing trend of home gardening in Lesotho (aligned with food security goals). It\'s a service-based business with extremely low startup costs, as you provide expertise and labor rather than materials or tools. Your carpentry skills can offer a unique selling proposition for more structured garden setups. \"Weekends-only\" fits perfectly for clients who are also available on weekends.', 'Licenses/Permits: M0 (Initial informal operation; register from first earnings if required by local ', 'Week 1-2:** Set up a professional WhatsApp profile. Announce your services in local community WhatsA', 'en', '2025-11-13 19:47:29', NULL),
(91, 5, 'Carpentry', 'Farming', 'Smartphone: ✓', '-29.389313, 27.524122', 'weekends-only', 'Local households and farmers often struggle to find skilled carpenters for small repairs (e.g., doors, windows, furniture) or custom structures (e.g., gates, fences, animal housing) without incurring high costs or the hassle of transporting items to a workshop. Many local residents seek unique, practical, and aesthetically pleasing wooden items for their homes and gardens (e.g., planter boxes, small outdoor benches, spice racks, shoe racks, custom shelving). Mass-produced alternatives are often expensive or don\'t fit specific needs. Many individuals or small entrepreneurs in the community want to undertake carpentry projects (e.g., building a small shed, custom furniture for a business, large garden structures) but lack the expert knowledge for proper design, accurate material estimation, or efficient construction techniques.', 'Weekend Handy Carpenter Mafeteng TimberCraft Weekend WoodWise Consulting', 'Offer on-site carpentry services during weekends in your local area. Focus on repairs for household items and building/repairing small wooden farm structures like fences, gates, chicken coops, rabbit hutches, or custom garden beds. The key is that clients provide all necessary materials (wood, nails, hinges, etc.) for each project, eliminating your need for upfront inventory costs. Your smartphone will be used for communication, scheduling, sending quotes, and local marketing via WhatsApp groups and social media. Design and create small, custom-made wooden items for local homes and gardens. Examples include raised garden beds, decorative planter boxes, sturdy outdoor stools, compact shoe racks, or bespoke wall shelves. The business operates on a strict pre-order basis: clients place an order, and a deposit (covering the cost of materials) is required upfront. This eliminates your need for initial stock capital. You produce the items on weekends, using your carpentry skills, and then deliver or arrange for client pickup, collecting the remaining payment. Your smartphone will showcase your designs (photos/sketches) and manage orders. Offer weekend-only consultation services where you leverage your carpentry skills to provide expert advice on DIY projects. Your service would include helping clients with project design, accurately calculating material quantities (wood, nails, etc.), offering step-by-step construction guidance, and suggesting cost-effective techniques. This is a purely knowledge-based service – the client executes the project, you provide the plan and guidance. Consultations can be done remotely (via phone/WhatsApp for designs and calculations) or on-site for specific project assessments.', 'This idea directly leverages your carpentry skills with zero upfront cash for materials. Operating on-site means no workshop rent. Your weekend availability is perfectly suited for this model. The Mafeteng area, being a mix of rural and peri-urban, has a consistent demand for such practical services from both households and small-scale farmers. This leverages your carpentry skills and allows for creative expression. The pre-order model completely removes the need for upfront material costs, making it viable with zero cash capital. Weekend-only production is perfectly manageable for small items. There is a demand for personalized, locally crafted goods in many communities. This idea perfectly matches your carpentry skills with absolutely zero cash outlay. It requires no tools or materials from your side, only your expertise and your smartphone. Your weekend availability is ideal. This service provides significant value to clients by helping them avoid costly mistakes and achieve better results, and is highly adaptable to a local community where DIY is common.', 'M0 initial cash outlay. Startup Cost Breakdown (Cash Outlay M0):** Business Registration/Permits: M0', 'Week 1-2:** Set up a professional WhatsApp Business profile. Join local community groups (WhatsApp, ', 'en', '2025-11-13 19:48:23', NULL),
(92, 1, 'Cooking', 'Technology', 'M5000', 'Maseru', 'full-time', 'Busy Basotho in Maseru often seek quick, affordable, and delicious hot meals or snacks during their day. This business provides convenient access to popular local street food. Busy professionals and households in Maseru often lack the time or resources to prepare traditional Basotho meals daily. This service offers convenient, authentic, and affordable home-cooked meals delivered to their doorstep. Many small shops and tuck shops in Maseru struggle to provide fresh, high-quality baked goods. This business offers a consistent supply of delicious, affordable muffins, scones, and small cakes, fulfilling a local market gap.', 'Lekunutu La Mpho\'s Kasi Bites Thabo\'s Bophelo Kitchen Maseru Muffins & More', 'This business involves operating a mobile food stall selling freshly made vetkoek with various fillings (e.g., mince, polony, atchar) and Sphatlho (Kota). You would target high-traffic areas such as taxi ranks, bus stops, informal markets, and busy pedestrian zones in Maseru. Your cooking skill is directly applied, and your interest in technology can be used for taking pre-orders via WhatsApp or promoting daily specials on community groups. Operating from your home kitchen, you would prepare popular traditional Basotho meals (e.g., Papa & Beef Stew, Chicken Stew, Mofofoli, Chakalaka). Customers would place orders via WhatsApp or phone, and you would deliver within Maseru, focusing on offices and residential areas. You can leverage your technology interest to manage orders, schedule deliveries, and create a simple digital menu. This business focuses on baking popular items like scones, muffins, and small cakes (e.g., cupcakes) from your home kitchen. You would primarily sell these wholesale to small grocery stores, tuck shops, and other local businesses, and also cater for small events or parties in Maseru. Your cooking skill would be used for baking, and your tech interest can help manage orders, client relationships, and simple marketing via social media.', 'High Demand:** Street food is a staple in Maseru, offering affordable and satisfying options. Low Overhead:** A mobile setup avoids costly commercial rent. Direct Skill Use:** Directly leverages your cooking expertise. Capital Efficiency:** M5000 is sufficient for essential equipment and initial stock. Tech Integration:** Easy to use a smartphone for marketing, customer communication, and orders. Leverages Cooking Skill:** Directly uses your primary skill. Home-based:** Eliminates the significant cost of commercial rent. Demand for Convenience:** Growing urban demand for ready-to-eat meals. Technology Integration:** Ideal for online orders, communication, and route planning. Manageable Capital:** M5000 is sufficient for supplementing kitchen equipment, initial stock, and delivery essentials. Uses Cooking Skill:** Directly applies your baking expertise. Home-based Operation:** Keeps startup and operational costs low by avoiding commercial rent. Market Opportunity:** Many small shops would prefer to buy fresh baked goods rather than bake them in-house. Manageable Production:** Baked goods can be produced in batches, allowing for efficient use of time. Capital Friendly:** M5000 is sufficient for essential baking tools, ingredients, and initial packaging.', 'M4,950 M4,900 M4,990', 'Licenses/Permits (M500):** Small Business Trading License (Maseru City Council): M300 Health & Hygie', 'en', '2025-11-13 19:48:59', NULL),
(93, 1, 'Cooking', 'Technology', 'M5000', 'Maseru', 'full-time', 'Busy individuals, office workers, and households in Maseru need convenient, affordable, home-cooked meals without the time or hassle of cooking. There\'s a demand for reliable, local meal delivery, especially for traditional comfort foods. People in high-footfall areas of Maseru (bus stops, taxi ranks, market areas, near offices/schools) often seek quick, affordable, and tasty snacks or light meals on the go. This fills a gap for convenient, accessible street food options. This taps into the robust informal economy, a vital sector in Lesotho. Individuals and small businesses in Maseru often need custom baked goods for events, celebrations, or as gifts, but struggle to find reliable small-scale suppliers offering personalized designs and convenient ordering.', '', 'Prepare a small, rotating menu of popular Basotho dishes or comfort meals (e.g., pap and stew, chicken portions, vetkoek and mince) from your home kitchen. Customers place orders via WhatsApp Business or a dedicated Facebook page. Deliveries are made within Maseru, initially using public transport or walking for nearby orders, focusing on offices and residential areas. Prepare popular Basotho snacks or light meals (e.g., fat cakes (mahoho), grilled maize, sausage rolls, small portions of papa & nyama/mokopu) from your home kitchen. Sell these from a mobile setup (small trolley or foldable table with a cooler box) at strategic busy locations in Maseru. Use WhatsApp/Facebook to announce daily locations, specials, or take pre-orders from nearby businesses. Specialize in a few popular baked items like custom cupcakes, birthday cakes, cookies, or traditional sweet treats (\'dikuku tsa leting\'). Focus on taking orders primarily through a visually appealing Facebook/Instagram page and WhatsApp Business, showcasing your creative designs. Prepare items from your home kitchen and arrange for customer pickup or small-scale local delivery. Technology interest can be used for creating engaging visual content and managing orders.', 'Directly uses cooking skills. Leverages technology interest for efficient order taking, marketing, and customer communication. Low overhead due to being home-based. Maseru\'s urban environment provides a clear customer base for convenient food options, as demand for prepared foods rises with urbanization. Directly utilizes cooking skills. Uses technology for marketing and location updates, attracting customers. Very low startup cost and high visibility. The mobile nature avoids fixed rent costs, which is crucial for the M5000 budget. Highly leverages baking skills, allowing for higher profit margins on customized items. Strong use of technology for visual marketing and efficient order management. Home-based operation keeps overhead low. Caters to a niche market for special occasions and personalized gifts.', 'M5000 Itemized Budget: Business Registration (Sole Proprietor DTI): M250 Food Handler\'s Certificate ', 'Week 1:** Register business with DTI, apply for Food Handler\'s Certificate. Research ingredient supp', 'en', '2025-11-13 19:59:49', NULL),
(94, 1, 'Cooking', 'Technology', 'M5000', 'Maseru', 'full-time', 'Busy residents, students, and workers in Maseru often need convenient, affordable, and tasty ready-to-eat meals and snacks, especially during lunch hours. Many opt for quick fixes due to time constraints, preferring home-style cooked food. Demand for fresh, high-quality, and custom-made baked goods (e.g., cakes for special occasions, specialty pastries, artisanal bread) often requires pre-ordering or is expensive from established bakeries. There\'s a gap for accessible, home-baked goodness with a personalized touch. Limited availability of unique, locally-sourced, and artisanal condiments (e.g., chili sauces, achaar, jams made from local fruits) and specialty preserved foods in Maseru. Many consumers seek healthier, more authentic alternatives to mass-produced items and ways to enjoy local flavours year-round.', 'Lijo Tsa Matla Maseru Custom Bakes Maseru Local Delights', 'Prepare and sell popular Basotho meals and snacks (e.g., pap and stew/fried chicken, moroho, fat cakes, samoosas) from a mobile street stall or trolley. Target high-footfall areas such as taxi ranks, bus stops, near government offices, schools, or university campuses. Leverage technology by accepting mobile money payments (M-Pesa, EcoCash) and using WhatsApp for pre-orders or daily menu updates to nearby offices/businesses. Operate a home-based bakery specializing in a limited range of high-demand items, such as customized celebration cakes, premium fat cakes, or unique savory pastries. Leverage technology heavily for marketing through social media (Facebook, Instagram, WhatsApp Business), taking orders, and accepting mobile money payments. Offer flexible options for customer pickup or local delivery (using public transport or a small fee). Produce small batches of high-quality, homemade preserves and condiments like chili sauces (e.g., \"peri-peri\" Basotho style), pickled vegetables (atchar), or fruit jams using seasonal local produce. Emphasize natural ingredients and unique flavour profiles. Sell through direct orders (WhatsApp), local farmers\' markets, and potentially supply small local shops or guesthouses. Technology can be used for recipe research, label design, and social media marketing to highlight the \"local\" and \"homemade\" aspects.', 'Skills:** Directly uses strong cooking skills. Interests:** Technology interest is vital for efficient order taking, payment processing, and quick social media marketing. Capital:** M5000 is sufficient for a basic, mobile setup, avoiding high rent costs. Location:** Maseru has a high demand for affordable street food, with a large working and student population. Market:** Immediate cash flow, high demand, and low barriers to entry. Skills:** Strong use of cooking and baking skills. Interests:** Technology is central for marketing, online order management, and digital payments, reaching a wider customer base from home. Capital:** Low initial overhead as it\'s home-based, eliminating external rent. Focus on quality ingredients and attractive packaging. Location:** Maseru\'s growing urban population, events, and family gatherings create a consistent demand for specialty baked goods. Market:** Higher-margin products for a niche market, with the flexibility of home operation. Skills:** Direct use of cooking and food preservation skills. Interests:** Technology for branding, recipe refinement, and online marketing to showcase products and reach customers. Capital:** Manageable for small-batch production using common kitchen equipment. Products are shelf-stable, reducing daily pressure and waste. Location:** Maseru\'s urban population and small businesses (like guesthouses) could be target customers for unique, local artisanal products. Market:** Niche market for gourmet, local food products with potential for higher profit margins and scalability.', 'M5000 Suggested budget: Sturdy foldable table & chair: M400 Gas stove (single burner) & 9kg gas cyli', 'Week 1:** Research prime vending locations in Maseru. Apply for and secure a street vending permit f', 'en', '2025-11-13 20:00:27', NULL),
(95, 1, 'Cooking', 'Technology', 'M5000', 'Maseru', 'full-time', 'Busy professionals and students in Maseru need convenient, affordable, and authentic home-style Basotho meals delivered to their workplaces or study locations during lunch hours, often preferring digital payment options. Commuters, shoppers, and workers in high-traffic areas of Maseru need quick, hot, affordable snacks and beverages, and increasingly prefer convenient digital payment options. Small businesses, organizations, and families in Maseru require affordable, quality catering for meetings, workshops, or private gatherings (e.g., 10-30 people) without the high cost associated with large catering companies.', 'Lijo Tsa Lapeng Express (Home Meals Express) Kuku le Kofi (Fat Cake & Coffee) Mobile Stand Maseru Home Catering & Events', 'Cook and deliver popular Basotho dishes like papa le nama (pap and meat), moroho (spinach/greens), motoho (fermented sorghum porridge), and stews from your home kitchen directly to offices, businesses, or designated pickup points in Maseru. Leverage your interest in technology by using WhatsApp and Facebook for menu sharing, order taking, and promotion, and facilitate payments via M-Pesa or EcoCash. Set up a small, mobile stand in a bustling Maseru location (e.g., near a taxi rank, market entrance, or bus stop) selling freshly made fat cakes (magwinya/vetkoeks), samosas, and instant tea/coffee. Your technology interest can be applied by prominently offering and accepting M-Pesa/EcoCash, making transactions faster and more convenient for customers. Offer bespoke catering services from your home kitchen for small events, focusing on traditional Basotho cuisine or popular comfort foods. Your interest in technology can be used to market your services widely on social media platforms (Facebook, Instagram) and facilitate inquiries, custom menu discussions, and bookings via WhatsApp or a simple online form, offering a modern touch to event planning.', 'This idea directly utilizes your cooking skills, has very low overhead (cooking from home eliminates rent), and integrates your technology interest for efficient operations and marketing. Maseru provides a large target market, and the M5000 capital is sufficient for a lean, home-based start. It addresses a consistent daily demand for food. This business leverages your cooking skills for high-demand, low-cost items with good profit margins. The mobile nature keeps startup costs low (no rent). Maseru\'s urban environment offers many suitable high-footfall locations, and the focus on digital payments aligns with your interest and local trends. It requires minimal initial stock and can generate quick daily revenue. This utilizes your cooking skills for higher-margin services than daily food sales. Operating from home minimizes rent. The tech integration for marketing and booking is efficient. While event frequency might be lower, the value per order is higher, allowing for good profit generation once a client base is established. The M5000 is feasible for a start by focusing on a \"cook-to-order\" model and initially renting larger items like chafing dishes when needed.', 'M5000 M4800 M4950', 'Week 1:** Business registration (Sole Proprietor/B.T.C.), obtaining a health certificate (if require', 'en', '2025-11-13 20:01:12', NULL),
(96, 5, 'Carpentry', 'Farming', 'Smartphone: ✓', '-29.389312, 27.524077', 'evenings', 'Households and small businesses in rural areas often struggle to find skilled carpenters for urgent repairs (broken furniture, doors, windows) or to create small, custom wooden items. Transporting items to a distant workshop is inconvenient and costly. Farmers looking to diversify income through beekeeping often lack access to affordable, locally-made beehives. Home gardeners and small-scale farmers also need practical solutions like raised beds and planters to maximize limited space and manage water efficiently. Small-scale farmers in your area often face challenges with basic farm infrastructure. They may need help with minor repairs to fences, building simple animal shelters, or setting up basic wooden supports for crops, but lack the skills, time, or tools. Access to practical agricultural advice can also be limited.', 'Ha Lebamang Handy Carpenter Maloti Woodcraft for Farm & Garden Mafeteng Farm Hand & Builder', 'Offer on-site carpentry repair services for homes and small businesses. Additionally, take orders for small custom wooden items like shelves, stools, garden planters, or basic fences. You will use your smartphone to market your services, communicate with clients, and manage orders. Focus on convenience by visiting clients directly. Using your carpentry skills, construct custom beehives (e.g., Langstroth or top-bar designs) for local beekeepers and build various sizes of raised garden beds and planters for home gardeners and small farmers. You will promote your designs using your smartphone, taking pre-orders and deposits to cover material costs. Offer targeted support services to local farmers. This includes building or repairing small wooden farm structures (e.g., fence posts, gates, simple chicken coops, crop trellises), constructing durable storage boxes for produce, and providing basic practical advice on farm setup or resource management using information you gather with your smartphone. Your carpentry skills are central to delivering physical solutions.', 'Skills:** Directly utilizes your carpentry expertise. Capital:** Leverages your smartphone for marketing. For repairs, customers often provide materials or you advise them on what to buy. For custom items, you will require a deposit for materials before starting work, ensuring no upfront material cost for you. Location:** Fills a common service gap in rural areas, where skilled tradespeople are not always readily available or mobile. Availability:** Repairs and measuring for custom orders can be scheduled for evenings, allowing you to work after any day commitments. Skills:** Excellent match for your carpentry expertise. Interests:** Directly supports your interest in farming and local agricultural practices. Capital:** Your smartphone is key for showcasing designs (photos/sketches), taking orders, and coordinating with clients. This model relies heavily on a **deposit system**: clients pay a significant portion (e.g., 50-70%) upfront, which you use to purchase the necessary wood and fasteners for their specific order. Location:** Caters directly to the local farming community and households seeking practical garden solutions. Beekeeping is an area of growing interest in Lesotho. Availability:** Construction can be done efficiently in the evenings or on weekends, allowing you to manage your time effectively. Skills:** Directly applies your carpentry skills to agricultural needs. Interests:** Deeply aligns with your interest in farming and supporting the local agricultural community. Capital:** Relies primarily on your smartphone for information gathering, communication, and basic marketing. For physical construction/repair jobs, clients either supply materials or pay for them upfront, keeping your initial cash outlay at M0. Location:** Directly serves the needs of the farming community in your area. Availability:** Physical construction or repair work can be scheduled flexibly for evenings or weekends, while information gathering can be done anytime.', 'Smartphone (✓):** Existing asset. Basic Hand Tools:** (Hammer, hand saw, measuring tape, chisel, scr', 'Week 1-2:** Spread the word using your smartphone in local WhatsApp groups, community gatherings, an', 'en', '2025-11-13 20:16:37', NULL);

